All Matters Construction – Internal Application End User License Agreement (EULA)

Last Updated: 11/22/2025

This End User License Agreement (“Agreement”) governs the use of the internal software application (“Application”) developed and maintained by All Matters Construction (“Company”). By accessing or using the Application, you (“User”) agree to be bound by this Agreement.

1. Purpose of the Application

The Application is an internal tool designed to retrieve read-only financial and project-related data from QuickBooks Online and other internal systems in order to generate reports and dashboards for operational use.

The Application is provided exclusively for the internal business purposes of All Matters Construction.

2. Authorized Users

Use of the Application is restricted to authorized employees and personnel of All Matters Construction, including:

Owners

Project Managers

Company General Manager

Designated IT administrators

No other individuals or parties are permitted to access or use the Application.

3. License Grant

The Company grants Users a limited, non-transferable, non-exclusive license to use the Application solely for internal business operations.

Users may not:

Distribute, publish, or share the Application externally

Copy or reproduce the Application except as necessary for authorized internal use

Reverse engineer, modify, or create derivative works

Use the Application for any illegal or unauthorized purpose

4. Data Access and Use

The Application accesses the following categories of internal Company data:

Invoices

Bills

Expenses

Payments

Estimates

Basic customer information

Project and job-related data

The Application is read-only and does not modify data in QuickBooks Online or any other system.

Users must handle all accessed data as confidential and may only use it for authorized business purposes.

5. Security Requirements

Users agree to:

Maintain the confidentiality of their login credentials

Prevent unauthorized access to the Application

Use the Application only on Company-approved devices and networks

Comply with all internal security and IT policies

The Company may monitor usage and audit access to ensure compliance.

6. Data Storage

The Application stores retrieved data in a local encrypted database located on an internal Windows server or workstation.

No data is transmitted to third parties outside of the Company’s environment except for internal reporting tools such as Power BI.

7. No Warranty

The Application is provided “as is” without any warranty of any kind, including but not limited to implied warranties of:

Performance

Accuracy

Fitness for a particular purpose

Non-infringement

The Company does not guarantee uninterrupted operation or error-free performance.

8. Limitation of Liability

To the maximum extent permitted by law, All Matters Construction shall not be liable for any indirect, incidental, consequential, or special damages arising out of or in connection with the use of the Application.

9. Termination

The Company may revoke access to the Application at any time for any reason, including violation of this Agreement or internal policies.

Upon termination, Users must immediately cease using the Application.

10. Updates

The Company may update, modify, or discontinue the Application at its discretion. Continued use after updates constitutes acceptance of the updated terms.

11. Contact Information

For questions or issues related to this Agreement or the Application, please contact:

